  "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "- Stages after StageIntermediateHash - can be disabled - if --prune.*.older=0\r\n- ChangeSets work: StageHashState, StageIntermediatHashes, Unwind of StageExec). It means: StageExec still must write FullImmutabilityThreshold amount of ChangeSets - even if --prune.h.older < FullImmutabilityThreshold. See variables `writeChangeSets` and `nextStagesExpectData`. (Please create test for this corner case - because if pruned node will have not-enough changeSets for re-org - there will be no way to repair it, only re-sync).\r\n\r\nFYI: this feature is part of \"mining edition\" roadmap. There we will disable all stages after IntermediateHashes.",
